                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d699">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Leishman</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Hay</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of the United States</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Constantinople</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1903-02-06">
                            <hi rend="italic">February 6, 1903</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>(Mr. Leishman reports that the minister for foreign affairs begs to be accorded a
                    few days’ grace, which Mr. Leishman has declined to do, but could not refuse to
                    submit the request to the Department.</p>
                <p>Mr. Leishman adds that he may possibly find it politic to grant two or three
                    days’ extra time at the last moment, but without authorization would not feel
                    warranted in so doing.)</p>
            </div>
        </body>
